    <IRS990ScheduleO documentId="IRS990ScheduleO-01" softwareId="21013422">
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Pt VI, Line 6</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THIS ORGANIZATION IS A MEMBERSHIP ORGANIZATION.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Pt VI, Line 7a</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS IS ELECTED ON A ROTATING BI-ANNUAL BASIS BY THE MEMBERS AT LARGE AT AN ANNUAL GENERAL MEMBERSHIP MEETING. ALL CURRENT MEMBERS MAY VOTE.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Pt VI, Line 7b</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>CHANGES TO BY-LAWS AND OTHER CHANGES ARE SUBJECT TO VOTE BY THE GENERAL MEMBERSHIP.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Pt VI, Line 11b</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE FORM 990 IS PREPARED BY OUR ACCOUNTANT AND THEN PRESENTED TO THE BOARD AT A REGULARLY SCHEDULED OR SPECIFICALLY HELD BOARD MEETING. THE DOCUMENT IS REVIEWED IN ITS ENTIRETY, QUESTIONS ARE ASKED BY BOARD MEMBERS, AND ANY NECESSARY CHANGES ARE MADE TO THE FORM 990. THE BOARD MEMBERS SIGN A DOCUMENT STATING THEY HAVE REVIEWED THE FORM 990, AND THEN THE RETURN IS FILED.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Pt VI, Line 12c</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>IF A SITUATION ARISES IN WHICH SOMEONE IS SUSPECTED OF HAVING A CONFLICT OF INTEREST, THAT PERSON IS ASKED TO STATE IN WRITING ANY POSSIBLE CONFLICTS. THAT PERSON IS THEN REMOVED FROM ANY SITUATION WHERE HE OR SHE WOULD HAVE A CONFLICT OF INTEREST.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Pt VI, Line 15a</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>AUSTIN ROWING CLUB'S EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR'S SALARY WAS SET BY A RESEARCH PROCESS CONDUCTED BY THE HUMAN RESOURCES COMMITTEE AND APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. COMPARABLE SALARIES WERE GATHERED FROM LOCAL ORGANIZATIONS AS WELL AS SIMILAR JOBS NATIONALLY. ADJUSTMENTS TO THIS SALARY ARE VETTED BY THE HR COMMITTEE AND APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Pt VI, Line 15b</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>OFFICERS ARE NOT COMPENSATED, AND THERE ARE NO KEY EMPLOYEES.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Pt VI, Line 19</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>GOVERNING DOCUMENTS ARE MADE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Pt XII, Line 1</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE ORGANIZATION USES THE MODIFIED CASH BASIS OF ACCOUNTING WHICH IS A MORE ACCURATE DESCRIPTION OF OUR ACCOUNTING METHOD. IN GENERAL, REVENUE AND THE RELATED ASSETS ARE RECOGNIZED WHEN RECEIVED RATHER THAN WHEN EARNED, AND EXPENSES ARE RECOGNIZED WHEN PAID RATHER THAN WHEN THE OBLIGATIONS ARE INCURRED. MODIFICATIONS INCLUDE REPORTING INVENTORY, PROPERTY AND EQUIPMENT AND RELATED DEPRECIATION, SALES AND PAYROLL TAXES PAYABLE, AND GIFT CARDS.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
    </IRS990ScheduleO>
